  "body": "Hi All \r\n\r\nOur private blockchain is using the IBFT2 Consensus protocols , at the beginning we defined which addresses are acting as validators   in our private EVM ,and we input relatived address (21 Validators addrees ) to the extraData property at our genesis file. However  we wanna [remove the validators] not by the RPC call , but wanna update the RAW data at the genesis instead .\r\nSo any solutions can suggest ? \r\n\r\nps . Becasue when using the rpc call to remove validators is work only on the network is healthy , but in case the chain down and need to restart all nodes , then the removed validotors will reactive again ",
